WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.880
Dre: So, Junior's been interning
at Stevens & Lido.

00:03.880 --> 00:05.500
[ Flatly ] Hey, guys.

00:05.500 --> 00:06.830
Thanks for the opportunity.

00:06.830 --> 00:09.040
And like starting any new job,

00:09.040 --> 00:10.790
there were some growing pains.

00:10.790 --> 00:12.830
Stevens & Lido.

00:12.830 --> 00:15.250
Oh, yes, ma'am, Mr. Stevens
is in the bathroom,

00:15.250 --> 00:16.040
so why don't you call back...
Bathroom?!

00:16.040 --> 00:17.620
...in like 30 minutes.
Hey!

00:17.620 --> 00:19.420
[ Muttering ] Cut it out!
I'm so sorry!

00:19.420 --> 00:22.080
45 minutes!
What are you talking --

00:22.080 --> 00:23.250
Don't answer
the phone anymore.

00:23.250 --> 00:25.080
♪♪

00:25.080 --> 00:27.460
Some major growing pains.

00:27.460 --> 00:28.830
Thanks for changing that.

00:28.830 --> 00:31.040
Allow me.
Thank you.

00:33.960 --> 00:35.420
I have a meeting!

00:37.580 --> 00:39.880
This almost
never happens!

00:39.880 --> 00:42.080
♪♪

00:42.080 --> 00:43.460
Which leads us to today.

00:45.080 --> 00:46.500
I'll have the Italian sub.

00:46.500 --> 00:47.500
Okeydoke.

00:47.500 --> 00:48.710
And to make it easy
on you,

00:48.710 --> 00:49.710
I'll get
the same thing.

00:49.710 --> 00:50.710
Just make sure my meat

00:50.710 --> 00:52.290
is on the outside
of the sandwich.

00:52.290 --> 00:54.460
I'm not even trying
to touch bread.

00:54.460 --> 00:56.290
[ Chuckles ] Got to keep
my shoulders sexy.

00:56.290 --> 00:58.460
Do you just, like,
not want bread?

00:58.460 --> 00:59.960
No.

00:59.960 --> 01:02.250
A sandwich with no bread
is just a pile of meat.

01:02.250 --> 01:03.500
Dude.

01:03.500 --> 01:05.500
Okay.
Uh, lettuce and tomato?

01:05.500 --> 01:06.960
Sure.

01:06.960 --> 01:08.380
Have them
put it in a bowl

01:08.380 --> 01:10.330
and chop it up and
throw some dressing on it.

01:10.330 --> 01:11.830
So, a-a salad.

01:11.830 --> 01:13.380
Oh, my God!

01:13.380 --> 01:16.120
Have you not
had a sandwich before?

01:16.120 --> 01:18.290
Is it...just me?

01:18.290 --> 01:21.710
It was taking him a while
to find his footing,

01:21.710 --> 01:24.080
but he was settling
into his role of intern.

01:24.080 --> 01:26.080
Hey, Dad.
I hope you don't mind...
[ Sighs ]

01:26.080 --> 01:27.460
...but I had
a couple of thoughts

01:27.460 --> 01:29.670
for the Southland Mutual
pitch today.

01:29.670 --> 01:31.290
Okay, well, I do mind.

01:31.290 --> 01:33.170
You're not ready.
How do you know?

01:33.170 --> 01:35.290
Because you gave me
Charlie's lunch.

01:35.290 --> 01:37.290
♪♪

01:40.080 --> 01:42.330
♪♪

01:42.330 --> 01:44.960
Woman: [ Peppy voice ]
Southland Mutual --
It's your money!

01:44.960 --> 01:46.670
[ Key clacks ]
Man: [ Excited voice ]
Southland Mutual --

01:46.670 --> 01:48.670
It's your money!
[ Key clacks ]

01:48.670 --> 01:50.040
Man #2: [ Serious voice ]
Southland Mutual --

01:50.040 --> 01:51.250
It's your money.

01:51.250 --> 01:53.250
Enough! Enough!

01:53.250 --> 01:54.670
You've actually
found voices

01:54.670 --> 01:56.830
more annoying
than my ex-wife,

01:56.830 --> 01:58.460
may she rest in peace.

01:58.460 --> 02:01.040
We are going back
to the drawing board.

02:01.040 --> 02:02.080
That is crap.
-Mm-hmm.

02:02.080 --> 02:03.250
I might have
a solution.

02:03.250 --> 02:04.750
What?

02:04.750 --> 02:05.750
If I may...

02:05.750 --> 02:07.000
You may not.

02:07.000 --> 02:08.120
No, no, no,
l-let him go.

02:08.120 --> 02:10.330
It's not like
I'll be embarrassed.

02:10.330 --> 02:11.460
What have you got?

02:12.620 --> 02:14.670
Know this,

02:14.670 --> 02:17.830
if the words "star" or "wars"
come out of your mouth,

02:17.830 --> 02:21.170
I will knock you into
a galaxy far, far away.

02:24.500 --> 02:26.120
Um...

02:26.120 --> 02:27.670
I think the slogan works.

02:27.670 --> 02:30.620
It's...you know, just missing
a little something.

02:30.620 --> 02:32.830
Like, uh...

02:32.830 --> 02:34.000
"Southland Mutual --

02:34.000 --> 02:35.620
It's your money...

02:35.620 --> 02:36.460
Yeah."

02:36.460 --> 02:38.120
Hate it.

02:38.120 --> 02:40.120
Hmm...

02:40.120 --> 02:41.250
Interesting.

02:41.250 --> 02:43.540
Yeah, that, too.

02:43.540 --> 02:44.580
I-If you like that,

02:44.580 --> 02:45.960
I thought about a "yes"
or a-a "yep."

02:45.960 --> 02:47.420
What about a-a "maybe"

02:47.420 --> 02:49.210
or a "okeydokey"
or a "damn straight"?

02:49.210 --> 02:51.000
Well, what about
a "yes"?

02:51.000 --> 02:52.000
What were you doing?

02:52.000 --> 02:53.250
You guys were stuck,

02:53.250 --> 02:54.420
and I thought
my idea might help.

02:54.420 --> 02:56.830
They always say a good idea
can come from anywhere.

02:56.830 --> 02:59.420
Yeah, it comes from people
who sit around this table.

02:59.420 --> 03:00.830
Leave the ad stuff
to us,

03:00.830 --> 03:03.710
and we'll leave the
"not knowing your place" to you.

03:03.710 --> 03:06.500
Yeah, and everyone leave
my laptop to me.

03:06.500 --> 03:08.330
This is
a real computer

03:08.330 --> 03:11.000
and not a toy
that sends zoo e-mails.

03:11.000 --> 03:12.880
But, wait, wh-what?

03:12.880 --> 03:14.500
Hmm?
But, guys,

03:14.500 --> 03:17.120
Mr. Stevens
liked my pitch.

03:17.120 --> 03:18.330
He said
it was interesting.

03:18.330 --> 03:20.880
You don't know what
"interesting" means.

03:20.880 --> 03:23.330
What if you took off
all of your clothes

03:23.330 --> 03:25.750
and your girlfriend says,
"Interesting"

03:25.750 --> 03:27.120
and then
leaves the room?

03:27.120 --> 03:28.500
Do you think
she's coming back?

03:28.500 --> 03:31.040
Depends -- is it hot
or cold in the room?

03:31.040 --> 03:32.170
Boy, that's not
the point!

03:33.210 --> 03:34.620
You spoke out of turn!

03:34.620 --> 03:36.080
You could have gotten
both of us fired.

03:36.080 --> 03:38.500
Oh. I'm sorry. I...

03:38.500 --> 03:39.710
I didn't realize that.

03:39.710 --> 03:40.920
Well...

03:40.920 --> 03:42.080
Well, I couldn't get fired

03:42.080 --> 03:44.250
'cause I have a very tight
lawsuit, but you?

03:44.250 --> 03:46.290
You don't have tapes.

03:46.290 --> 03:49.080
[ Laughs ] You blew it,
college boy.

03:49.080 --> 03:50.880
Your days
are numbered here.

03:50.880 --> 03:53.710
[ Lion roaring ]

03:53.710 --> 03:55.500
Excuse me.

03:55.500 --> 03:56.880
I have to
go handle this...

03:56.880 --> 03:58.500
business.

03:58.500 --> 04:00.920
♪♪

04:00.920 --> 04:02.580
-What you guys doing?
-Quiet.

04:02.580 --> 04:04.830
She concentrating
on my science homework.

04:04.830 --> 04:06.460
Hey, hey, hey,
get a few wrong

04:06.460 --> 04:07.750
so that they know I did it.
[ Chuckles ]

04:07.750 --> 04:10.250
You know that's the Stunts'
brand and everything, so...

04:10.250 --> 04:12.210
Stunts, it's actually
pretty interesting.

04:12.210 --> 04:13.420
If you just --
-Pass.

04:13.420 --> 04:15.420
So, uh,
where's Dr. Bow at?

04:15.420 --> 04:17.040
I got a weird mole
I want to show her.

04:17.040 --> 04:19.460
She's meeting
with Mrs. Keeley.

04:19.460 --> 04:20.710
You're letting Mom go to
a parent-teacher conference?

04:20.710 --> 04:22.210
Ugh, rookie move.

04:22.210 --> 04:23.500
Are you supposed
to have street smarts?

04:23.500 --> 04:24.790
We told her
that they stopped doing

04:24.790 --> 04:26.540
parent-teacher conferences
years ago.

04:26.540 --> 04:27.670
Yeah.

04:27.670 --> 04:28.750
She also believes
we don't get grades

04:28.750 --> 04:30.620
during the month
of Ramadan.

04:30.620 --> 04:32.210
Look, the point is,

04:32.210 --> 04:33.710
she's going
to embarrass you,

04:33.710 --> 04:34.920
like when she dances.

04:34.920 --> 04:35.920
And it's gonna be sad...

04:35.920 --> 04:37.210
like when she dances.

04:37.210 --> 04:38.830
She's just talking
to a teacher.

04:38.830 --> 04:39.960
How bad can it be?

04:39.960 --> 04:41.540
♪♪

04:41.540 --> 04:43.170
What's the deal-y,
Mrs. Keeley?

04:43.170 --> 04:45.710
Give me the real-y.
[ Laughs ]

04:45.710 --> 04:47.620
I've got 40 more parents
after this.
Oh, that's fine.

04:47.620 --> 04:49.000
Yep. Mm-hmm.

04:49.000 --> 04:51.620
Here's some of Kyra's
most recent test scores.

04:51.620 --> 04:53.120
Oh, okay.

04:53.120 --> 04:54.790
[ Groaning ]

04:56.380 --> 04:58.250
Oh, my goodness.

04:58.250 --> 05:00.920
Oh! She aced these!

05:00.920 --> 05:02.960
Mm-hmm.
[ Chuckles ]
Oh. Uh-oh.

05:02.960 --> 05:04.670
Got that one wrong,
right there, actually.

05:04.670 --> 05:06.380
There's only
114 elements,

05:06.380 --> 05:07.960
unless they added four
that I don't know about.

05:07.960 --> 05:09.540
[ Chuckles ]
They did.

05:09.540 --> 05:10.830
They --
They, uh --

05:10.830 --> 05:13.790
Oh. Okay. Well...

05:13.790 --> 05:15.880
guess that's why
you're the teacher...

05:17.120 --> 05:19.330
...and I am the doctor.
[ Chuckles ]

05:19.330 --> 05:21.040
So anyway...

05:21.040 --> 05:23.460
Kyra has a real aptitude
for chemistry.

05:23.460 --> 05:25.330
I mean,
she's really drawn to it.

05:25.330 --> 05:27.710
She gets that from me.
Yeah.

05:27.710 --> 05:29.120
I mean, I know she's only
been with us

05:29.120 --> 05:30.170
for, like,
a short amount of time,

05:30.170 --> 05:32.670
but I make
a big impression.

05:32.670 --> 05:34.540
I can see that.
[ Chuckles ]
Is it the shoulders?

05:34.540 --> 05:37.250
Giveaway? [ Laughs ]
Brr!

05:37.250 --> 05:39.620
So, there is
a magnet school nearby

05:39.620 --> 05:41.710
that I think
she'd be great for.

05:41.710 --> 05:43.170
That's incredible.

05:43.170 --> 05:45.120
Oh, my God,
she must be so excited.

05:45.120 --> 05:48.000
Oh, no.
She is not into it.

05:48.000 --> 05:49.170
What?!
Every time
I bring it up,

05:49.170 --> 05:50.750
she blows me off.
Huh.

05:50.750 --> 05:52.580
I just can't
get through to her.

05:52.580 --> 05:54.670
Well, I-I will
talk to her

05:54.670 --> 05:56.880
because this is --
this is a big opportunity.

05:56.880 --> 05:59.880
I will tell her how attractive
a magnet school can be.

05:59.880 --> 06:01.790
Oh, my God, I didn't even know
I just did that.

06:01.790 --> 06:02.750
Did you hear that?
[ Laughs ]

06:02.750 --> 06:03.920
Thank you, Dr. Johnson.

06:03.920 --> 06:06.210
Yep. Yep, okay.

06:08.290 --> 06:09.790
I'll try one more.
Thank you.

06:09.790 --> 06:11.040
Hey -- Ooh.

06:11.040 --> 06:13.920
♪♪

06:13.920 --> 06:15.620
Ah!

06:15.620 --> 06:17.210
Tough afternoon, huh?

06:17.210 --> 06:18.830
Yeah, but you learned
to listen to me

06:18.830 --> 06:21.040
and not ignore
my years of experience.

06:21.040 --> 06:22.500
You won't
do that again.

06:22.500 --> 06:24.210
No, I won't.
Mm.

06:24.210 --> 06:25.790
I just thought
I had a good idea.

06:25.790 --> 06:28.170
Of course you didn't!

06:28.170 --> 06:30.420
You haven't had
a good idea in a while.

06:30.420 --> 06:32.670
Like, leaving Howard...
[ Chuckles ]

06:32.670 --> 06:34.210
...that shirt.

06:34.210 --> 06:36.290
Come on, son.
You're right.

06:36.290 --> 06:38.250
I really feel like
I stepped on some toes.

06:38.250 --> 06:40.540
Charlie won't stop
texting me GIFs

06:40.540 --> 06:42.290
of people getting
knocked out.

06:42.290 --> 06:44.120
Look, this is
a teachable moment.

06:44.120 --> 06:45.380
You messed up,

06:45.380 --> 06:46.710
but you can make it right

06:46.710 --> 06:48.330
by working twice as hard.

06:48.330 --> 06:50.620
You're not gonna
be a superstar overnight.

06:50.620 --> 06:52.580
Ah!
There's our superstar!

06:52.580 --> 06:53.880
What?

06:53.880 --> 06:56.080
Junior, the client
loved your tag line.

06:56.080 --> 06:57.880
Really?
Yeah, they did.

06:57.880 --> 06:59.880
And I said there's
nobody we'll find

06:59.880 --> 07:01.620
who says it
better than you.

07:01.620 --> 07:03.170
So, we're just
gonna have you record it.

07:03.170 --> 07:05.170
Now,
important question --

07:05.170 --> 07:06.710
do you have an agent?

07:06.710 --> 07:07.670
Uh, no.

07:07.670 --> 07:09.670
Perfect! Yeah.

07:09.670 --> 07:12.040
We'll just have you sign
a standard Motown Contract.

07:12.040 --> 07:14.040
Oh.
But he has to get
our coffees first, right?

07:14.040 --> 07:15.580
Please, please.

07:15.580 --> 07:16.880
We'll get someone less
important for that job.

07:16.880 --> 07:19.290
Uh, Josh!
-Yes, boss?

07:19.290 --> 07:21.250
-You're on coffee.
-[ Dejectedly ] Yes, boss...

07:21.960 --> 07:23.330
Take notice, Dre.

07:23.330 --> 07:25.670
One day, we could all
be working for your son.

07:25.670 --> 07:26.670
[ Chuckles ]

07:26.670 --> 07:28.000
Great shirt.
Thank you.

07:31.420 --> 07:32.670
It's okay, Dad.

07:32.670 --> 07:34.790
Look at this
as a teachable moment.

07:34.790 --> 07:37.250
A good idea
can come from anywhere...

07:37.250 --> 07:38.830
Yeah.

07:38.830 --> 07:41.080
♪♪

07:44.540 --> 07:46.040
-Mom!
-Yeah?

07:46.040 --> 07:47.080
-Big news!
-Ooh!

07:47.080 --> 07:48.750
-Medium news.
-Tell me.

07:48.750 --> 07:51.670
I am the new voice of
the Southland Mutual campaign!

07:51.670 --> 07:53.250
What?!

07:53.250 --> 07:54.580
Oh, my God!

07:54.580 --> 07:55.830
That is huge!

07:55.830 --> 07:57.330
Voiceover.

07:57.330 --> 07:58.920
-Yep.
-Okay, d-do me a favor.

07:58.920 --> 08:00.540
Say this for me.

08:00.540 --> 08:02.170
[ Dramatically ]
"Previously, on 'Top Chef'..."

08:02.170 --> 08:03.250
-Previous--
-Okay, it's not huge, okay?

08:03.250 --> 08:04.620
The client just liked

08:04.620 --> 08:06.290
a little pitch that he made,
all right,

08:06.290 --> 08:07.960
so he's just
recording a demo.

08:07.960 --> 08:10.000
It's nothing
to congratulate him about.
Congratulations!

08:10.000 --> 08:12.210
It's nothing
to congratulate --
Thanks, Mom.

08:12.210 --> 08:13.750
I'm gonna go upstairs
and find out

08:13.750 --> 08:16.790
how much bank
Flo the Progressive lady makes.

08:16.790 --> 08:17.880
-All right.
-That is being proactive.

08:17.880 --> 08:20.080
-Whoo!
-[ Laughs ]

08:20.080 --> 08:22.120
All right.
That's exciting.

08:22.120 --> 08:24.210
This is terrifying.
What?

08:24.210 --> 08:26.790
The whole point of me
taking him to work with
me during his gap year

08:26.790 --> 08:28.960
was so that he could get
some real-life experience.

08:28.960 --> 08:30.710
It sounds like
that's what he's getting.

08:30.710 --> 08:32.670
Getting lucky
is not real-life experience.
[ Sighs ]

08:32.670 --> 08:34.420
What happens
when the luck runs out.

08:34.420 --> 08:36.170
How do you know
his luck's gonna run out?

08:36.170 --> 08:38.380
It's luck, Bow!
That's what it does.

08:38.380 --> 08:39.710
Oh, my God.

08:39.710 --> 08:41.750
That's why Pops was
so hard on me growing up,

08:41.750 --> 08:43.250
because he didn't want me
to get caught off guard

08:43.250 --> 08:44.250
when the other shoe
dropped.

08:44.250 --> 08:45.670
I thought
Pops was hard on you

08:45.670 --> 08:48.170
because you look so much
like Ruby around the eyes.

08:48.170 --> 08:50.250
That didn't help.
Mm.

08:50.250 --> 08:51.620
But Pops was right.

08:51.620 --> 08:55.210
You know, maybe Junior
does well tomorrow.
Mm.

08:55.210 --> 08:56.670
He gets signed,
he makes some money,

08:56.670 --> 08:58.080
he impresses a girl.
[ Gasps ]

08:58.080 --> 09:00.000
But the girl only likes him
because he's on a hot streak.

09:00.000 --> 09:02.000
Voice work runs out,
so does the girl.

09:02.000 --> 09:03.250
Now he can't sleep.

09:03.250 --> 09:05.460
Stress builds!
He needs a nightcap!

09:05.460 --> 09:07.670
The booze doesn't work,
so he turns to medicine.

09:07.670 --> 09:09.080
Medicine turns to pills,

09:09.080 --> 09:10.380
and the pills
he thinks is good

09:10.380 --> 09:12.080
because they come
from a doctor.

09:12.080 --> 09:13.380
Are you on pills
right now?

09:13.380 --> 09:15.250
No, I'm not
on pills, Bow.

09:15.250 --> 09:16.540
I'm just thinking
about our son

09:16.540 --> 09:18.500
ending up in front of
a hardware store,

09:18.500 --> 09:21.540
trying to earn $10
the best way that he can!

09:21.540 --> 09:23.960
Okay. Yeah.

09:23.960 --> 09:25.670
You are ridiculous.

09:25.670 --> 09:26.920
-Me? I'm ridiculous?
-Yeah. Mm-hmm.

09:26.920 --> 09:28.710
Okay,
s-sex for money, Bow!

09:30.330 --> 09:32.040
Or him helping
somebody build a deck!

09:32.040 --> 09:34.500
Either way, our son's gonna
be wearing tight shorts!

09:34.500 --> 09:36.120
♪♪

09:36.120 --> 09:37.880
[ Knock on door ]

09:37.880 --> 09:40.040
Hey, Special K.

09:40.040 --> 09:41.380
That's a drug reference,
Dr. Bow.

09:41.380 --> 09:42.170
Is it?

09:43.830 --> 09:45.710
I knew that.
[ Chuckles ]

09:45.710 --> 09:49.210
I came in here to talk to you
about getting high...

09:49.210 --> 09:50.670
on opportunity.

09:50.670 --> 09:52.040
[ Laughs ]

09:52.040 --> 09:54.290
Yeah, sweetheart, listen.

09:54.290 --> 09:59.080
Um, so,
Mrs. Keeley told me

09:59.080 --> 10:00.830
about
the magnet school.

10:00.830 --> 10:02.420
[ Whispering ]
I'm so excited.

10:02.420 --> 10:04.170
So she also told you
I'm not interested.

10:04.170 --> 10:06.170
[ Louder ]
What?! Why not?

10:06.170 --> 10:09.710
No, Kyra, this is a chance
to get a leg up in life.

10:09.710 --> 10:11.380
You -- You got to --

10:11.380 --> 10:13.580
You got to take these
opportunities when they come.

10:13.580 --> 10:15.920
I just see so much

10:15.920 --> 10:17.960
untapped potential...
Untapped potential.

10:17.960 --> 10:19.290
...in you,

10:19.290 --> 10:20.620
and it's just that
you're -- you're a

10:20.620 --> 10:22.460
leader, not a follower.
Leader, not a follower.

10:22.460 --> 10:23.830
Yes.

10:24.580 --> 10:25.580
Yes.

10:25.580 --> 10:27.540
And I-I just think

10:27.540 --> 10:28.710
you would really
benefit from --

10:28.710 --> 10:30.000
A change of scenery.

10:30.000 --> 10:31.250
Maybe.

10:31.250 --> 10:34.460
Ooh, my girl's psychic,
psychic.

10:34.460 --> 10:37.250
That's not
what psychic is...

10:37.250 --> 10:39.500
Yeah, I've heard
these speeches a lot.

10:39.500 --> 10:42.000
Kyra, I just...

10:42.000 --> 10:44.380
I feel like
you should change schools.

10:44.380 --> 10:47.460
I think you should be somewhere
that has more to offer.

10:47.460 --> 10:49.290
I'm good
right where I'm at.

10:49.290 --> 10:50.790
-Kyra...
-I know what's best for me.

10:50.790 --> 10:51.830
You don't even
really know me.

10:51.830 --> 10:54.120
I know you!

10:54.120 --> 10:55.290
What's
my middle name?

10:55.290 --> 10:56.670
-Ah -- Psh, ah --
-Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh.

10:56.670 --> 10:57.670
What's her
favorite color?

10:57.670 --> 10:58.540
Uh...
[ Blows raspberry] Ah!

10:58.540 --> 10:59.920
[ Laughs ]

10:59.920 --> 11:02.790
Turquoise...for both.
What?

11:02.790 --> 11:04.750
Kyra...Turquoise

11:04.750 --> 11:06.040
loves turquoise.

11:06.040 --> 11:07.000
-Come on.
-Okay.

11:07.000 --> 11:09.170
Up we go.
All right.

11:09.170 --> 11:10.830
Well, listen,
I -- Okay.
We're just gonna
finish up our homework.

11:10.830 --> 11:12.290
I just want
to be honest, though.
Yeah.

11:12.290 --> 11:14.170
I am terrible
with middle names.

11:14.170 --> 11:16.540
I do not even know if I gave
Devante a middle name,

11:16.540 --> 11:18.960
so it's not like
I would've asked you that.
Yeah.

11:18.960 --> 11:20.830
-Mm-hmm.
-Okay. So...

11:20.830 --> 11:24.000
Dre: So Junior was set
to record the voiceover,

11:24.000 --> 11:26.670
and I knew the right thing
to do as a father

11:26.670 --> 11:29.170
was to root for him to fail,

11:29.170 --> 11:30.830
and it looked like
it was happening

11:30.830 --> 11:33.620
in front of the client and all.

11:33.620 --> 11:35.790
[ Metal creaking ]

11:35.790 --> 11:38.580
I...am so sorry.

11:38.580 --> 11:39.960
Don't worry about it.
Let's try one.

11:39.960 --> 11:42.170
-All right.
-Okay.

11:42.170 --> 11:44.380
Hey, give it
your best shot, son.

11:44.380 --> 11:46.000
All right.
[ Exhales sharply ]

11:47.380 --> 11:48.880
Southland Mutual --

11:48.880 --> 11:50.580
It's your money...

11:50.580 --> 11:51.420
Yeah.

11:51.420 --> 11:53.120
Perfect.
What?

11:53.120 --> 11:54.670
You nailed it!
What?!

11:54.670 --> 11:56.380
Did I get the job?
No.

11:56.380 --> 11:58.670
Yes. You're the voice
of Southland Mutual.

11:58.670 --> 12:00.250
-All right!
-But he only did it o--

12:00.250 --> 12:03.170
Dre! Right, the client's happy,
we're happy.

12:03.170 --> 12:04.620
Hey, that's lunch,
everybody!

12:04.620 --> 12:05.830
Josh!
-All right!

12:06.920 --> 12:08.620
[ Metal clangs ]

12:08.620 --> 12:10.040
What?

12:10.040 --> 12:11.120
♪♪

12:11.120 --> 12:13.290
[ Clicks tongue ]
Yes, okay.

12:13.290 --> 12:15.080
What's all this?
Everything you need

12:15.080 --> 12:17.210
to convince
a young girl

12:17.210 --> 12:20.170
how rewarding
a life in science can be.

12:20.170 --> 12:22.080
This is
my med school diploma,

12:22.080 --> 12:24.120
these are
medical journals

12:24.120 --> 12:25.790
that I've been published in,
and...

12:25.790 --> 12:27.540
[ Clears throat ]
...an ATM receipt.

12:27.540 --> 12:30.170
Yes, I know it's
a little crass, but...

12:30.170 --> 12:31.620
it's proof.

12:31.620 --> 12:33.830
I get paid.
I mean, it's a --

12:33.830 --> 12:36.170
it's a little low 'cause
we just paid the property tax,

12:36.170 --> 12:37.290
but you see how --
Look at that.

12:37.290 --> 12:40.420
All of this
is to convince Kyra

12:40.420 --> 12:43.120
that she should transfer
to the magnet school.

12:43.120 --> 12:44.670
Come on, Mom.

12:44.670 --> 12:46.790
Her school is where Stunts
and all her friends are.

12:46.790 --> 12:47.880
[ Cellphone clicks ]

12:47.880 --> 12:50.120
Look how happy she is.

12:50.120 --> 12:51.380
[ Indistinct talking,
music plays on cellphone ]

12:51.380 --> 12:53.580
Rainbow: Oh, wow.
Check that out.

12:53.580 --> 12:55.710
[ Laughter ]

12:55.710 --> 12:58.460
She does look happy.

12:58.460 --> 13:00.750
Yeah, I guess that would
be hard, you know,

13:00.750 --> 13:02.460
leaving all your friends,
starting all over again.

13:02.460 --> 13:03.750
Exactly.

13:03.750 --> 13:06.040
Why do you think I haven't
applied to clown college?

13:06.040 --> 13:08.380
Because I got
the grades.

13:08.380 --> 13:10.170
Oh, look,
you're in this one.
Diane: Kyra, you guys,
check this out.

13:10.170 --> 13:11.880
Ooh! Oh, you do not
need to see th--
Oh!

13:11.880 --> 13:14.040
"I'm Dr. Johnson.
I keep on having babies

13:14.040 --> 13:16.290
even though
I know how bodies work.

13:16.290 --> 13:18.880
And I get paid!
[ Laughter ]

13:18.880 --> 13:21.250
[ Chuckles ]
I mean, that --

13:21.250 --> 13:23.170
that could've been
any Dr. Johnson.

13:24.120 --> 13:25.580
[ Chuckles ]

13:25.580 --> 13:27.960
I haven't had a baby
in two years, little girl!

13:27.960 --> 13:30.290
♪♪

13:30.290 --> 13:32.250
Stevens: That put out
the fire completely.

13:32.250 --> 13:33.710
-Oh.
-Yeah.

13:33.710 --> 13:35.210
Hey!
There he is.

13:35.210 --> 13:38.000
Hey, we're just having some,
uh, celebration cake for Junior.

13:38.000 --> 13:39.460
-Really?
-Yeah.

13:39.460 --> 13:41.540
Yesterday, he was
a lowly intern.

13:41.540 --> 13:42.960
Today, he's the voice
of a regional bank.

13:42.960 --> 13:44.330
-Mm.
-Uh-huh.

13:44.330 --> 13:45.960
And tomorrow,
we'll be staying

13:45.960 --> 13:47.540
at Circus Circus
in Las Vegas.

13:47.540 --> 13:48.540
[ Chuckles ]

13:48.540 --> 13:49.960
[ Whispering ]
Check your inbox.

13:49.960 --> 13:51.880
There's a bill for a two-night
stay at Circus Circus.

13:51.880 --> 13:53.380
So you guys
are just...

13:53.380 --> 13:54.790
handing out cake now?

13:54.790 --> 13:57.120
Dre, you once demanded cake
when you parked really good.

13:57.120 --> 13:58.750
I backed in.

13:58.750 --> 14:01.120
D-Dad, just have
a slice of cake.

14:01.120 --> 14:02.290
No, I'm -- I'm good, son.
Thank you.

14:02.290 --> 14:05.210
-Come on, Dre.
-Hey, I'm a diabetic.

14:05.210 --> 14:07.170
That didn't stop you
when we had that cake

14:07.170 --> 14:08.790
that was shaped
like a pair of Jordans.

14:08.790 --> 14:11.290
You ate the laces like you were
"Lady and the Tramp."

14:11.290 --> 14:12.670
Okay, well,
y-you know what, man?

14:12.670 --> 14:14.290
I'm -- I'm more of
a cookies kind of guy.

14:14.290 --> 14:15.880
That's your favorite
topping for cakes.

14:15.880 --> 14:18.420
-[ Chuckles ]
-Dad, just have a small piece.

14:18.420 --> 14:20.710
I don't want the damn cake,
all right!

14:23.380 --> 14:25.750
[ Dish clatters ]

14:25.750 --> 14:27.880
What is your problem?!

14:27.880 --> 14:29.880
First,
I can't speak up.

14:29.880 --> 14:32.670
And then I do say something
and kill it twice,

14:32.670 --> 14:35.620
and you still
can't give it up for me!

14:35.620 --> 14:37.170
Why can't you celebrate
my success

14:37.170 --> 14:38.710
for even a second?!

14:41.210 --> 14:42.380
You know what?
It's whatever.

14:42.380 --> 14:47.960
♪♪

14:47.960 --> 14:49.460
Wow, Dre.

14:49.460 --> 14:52.460
You are a bad dad.

14:52.460 --> 14:54.040
And I never felt
so close to you in my life.

14:56.040 --> 14:57.080
We're gonna
get through this.

15:01.040 --> 15:03.420
[ Door closes ]
Oh...

15:03.420 --> 15:04.960
Hey, Pops.

15:04.960 --> 15:06.750
Can I talk to you
for a second?

15:06.750 --> 15:08.830
I knew I should've read
the paper in the library.

15:08.830 --> 15:10.380
Go ahead.

15:10.380 --> 15:13.460
Look, when I get bored,
I'm leaving.
Okay.

15:13.460 --> 15:15.580
So you may have heard
that Junior's had

15:15.580 --> 15:17.380
a little
overnight success.

15:17.380 --> 15:18.750
Yeah.

15:18.750 --> 15:20.290
Already borrowed
100 bucks from him.

15:20.290 --> 15:21.920
[ Chuckles ]
He thought it was a loan.

15:21.920 --> 15:24.380
[ Laughs ]

15:24.380 --> 15:26.210
Mm.

15:26.210 --> 15:27.460
So what's
the problem?

15:27.460 --> 15:29.290
Me.

15:29.290 --> 15:32.790
I basically hated on him
every step of the way.

15:32.790 --> 15:33.920
All I was worried about

15:33.920 --> 15:35.620
was making sure
he was ready for failure,

15:35.620 --> 15:37.580
but, Pops...

15:37.580 --> 15:39.670
he hasn't failed.
Oh...

15:39.670 --> 15:41.290
I never had
that problem with you.

15:41.290 --> 15:44.330
You're in uncharted waters, boy.
Hmm.

15:44.330 --> 15:47.420
So I'm supposed to just keep
preparing him for failure?

15:47.420 --> 15:49.040
Yeah, if you want
to be a good father.

15:49.040 --> 15:50.670
The world is hard.

15:50.670 --> 15:53.040
That means you got
to be hard on him

15:53.040 --> 15:55.790
so that nothing in life
sneaks up on him.
Hmm.

15:55.790 --> 15:57.710
Catches him off guard.
Mm-hmm.

15:57.710 --> 15:59.620
Like, uh...

15:59.620 --> 16:01.790
when you made
the football team.

16:01.790 --> 16:03.830
Oh, man,
I was so excited.

16:03.830 --> 16:05.580
I ran inside
to tell you,

16:05.580 --> 16:08.080
and all you could say was
I was too small and too fat

16:08.080 --> 16:09.000
and was never
gonna play.

16:09.000 --> 16:10.000
And I was right.

16:10.000 --> 16:11.290
You never did play

16:11.290 --> 16:12.580
because you were too small
and too fat.

16:12.580 --> 16:13.920
Ah...

16:13.920 --> 16:15.790
Everybody called me
Mini-Fridge.
See!

16:15.790 --> 16:17.620
I kept it real
with you, son.

16:17.620 --> 16:19.750
'Cause I knew the world was
gonna keep it real with you.

16:19.750 --> 16:21.000
[ Exhaling ] Yeah...

16:22.290 --> 16:24.460
Yeah.

16:24.460 --> 16:26.210
And...

16:26.210 --> 16:28.420
it wouldn't have killed me
to let you have your moment.

16:28.420 --> 16:29.620
Really?

16:29.620 --> 16:30.790
Oh, yeah, son.

16:30.790 --> 16:32.540
It was a big deal
that you made the team

16:32.540 --> 16:33.960
on account of your height
and your weight.

16:35.920 --> 16:37.000
Thank you, Pops.

16:37.000 --> 16:39.500
Mm-hmm.

16:39.500 --> 16:41.250
Say, you know what?
Maybe it's not too late for me

16:41.250 --> 16:42.830
to have this conversation
with Junior about --
[ Groans ]

16:42.830 --> 16:44.830
It's -- it's -- I --
Oh, good Lord.

16:44.830 --> 16:46.880
Good talking
to you, too.

16:46.880 --> 16:49.500
[ Door closes ]

16:49.500 --> 16:50.420
♪♪

16:50.420 --> 16:52.540
Hey, Kyra!

16:52.540 --> 16:53.710
I got your laundry!

16:53.710 --> 16:56.000
That's not my laundry.
It's Diane's.

16:56.000 --> 16:57.750
Oh...silly me.

16:57.750 --> 16:59.000
Oh! [ Chuckles ]

16:59.000 --> 17:01.380
Well, I'm here,
so let's talk.

17:03.460 --> 17:04.880
So...
[ Exhales deeply ]

17:07.330 --> 17:09.710
I think I know why
you don't want to transfer.

17:11.040 --> 17:12.620
You don't want to leave
your friends behind.

17:12.620 --> 17:14.330
Nice try, but I really
just don't want to

17:14.330 --> 17:16.040
start all over again.
Start all over again.

17:16.040 --> 17:16.960
What?

17:16.960 --> 17:19.120
No. Mnh-mnh.

17:19.120 --> 17:21.380
I just feel like I've

17:21.380 --> 17:23.420
had enough change already.
Had enough change already.

17:23.420 --> 17:24.500
Stop it.
Mm.

17:26.920 --> 17:28.580
I just --
I'm just saying that --

17:28.580 --> 17:30.830
That you don't want
to leave your friends

17:30.830 --> 17:32.620
and your school?

17:32.620 --> 17:34.040
Because they're the only
constant things

17:34.040 --> 17:36.330
you've had
in your life?

17:36.330 --> 17:37.750
Maybe.

17:37.750 --> 17:39.420
I know it's hard to leave
everything that you know,

17:39.420 --> 17:44.080
but...what if we find you
a great school

17:44.080 --> 17:46.540
where you already
know people?

17:46.540 --> 17:48.120
What are you
talking about?

17:48.120 --> 17:50.250
Bow-Bow's got ideas.

17:50.250 --> 17:52.920
♪♪

17:52.920 --> 17:54.040
[ Insects chirping ]

17:56.250 --> 17:57.620
Hey, son.
How's it going?

17:59.380 --> 18:00.540
Are you drinking?

18:00.540 --> 18:02.420
Nah, it's a mocktail.

18:02.420 --> 18:04.290
Helps take
the edge off.

18:04.290 --> 18:05.960
[ Slurps ]

18:05.960 --> 18:08.250
Smooth.
Ah.

18:08.250 --> 18:09.710
Well, maybe

18:09.710 --> 18:11.250
it'll pair well
with this.

18:11.250 --> 18:12.710
But, Dad, I had cake.

18:12.710 --> 18:15.040
The problem was
you wouldn't have any.

18:15.040 --> 18:16.380
Damn it, son,
I'm trying, okay?!

18:16.380 --> 18:17.750
It's called
a grand gesture!

18:17.750 --> 18:18.920
It -- Forget it.

18:18.920 --> 18:20.210
[ Cupcake splats ]

18:21.380 --> 18:22.540
Look, son...

18:25.540 --> 18:28.120
I just want to say
that I'm proud of you.

18:28.120 --> 18:30.710
You know, you spoke up
at work,

18:30.710 --> 18:31.920
you spoke --
Oh, yeah, man, it just --

18:31.920 --> 18:33.580
It just felt like the right
thing to do, you know.

18:33.580 --> 18:34.620
Okay, but that's not
what I'm proud of.

18:34.620 --> 18:36.040
All right.

18:36.040 --> 18:37.790
But after that,

18:37.790 --> 18:39.790
you got a shot at recording.
Thanks, Dad.

18:39.790 --> 18:41.170
You know, it -- it really
just clicked when I --

18:41.170 --> 18:43.670
But that's not what
I'm proud of, either.

18:43.670 --> 18:46.830
You got lucky, and
they liked what you did,

18:46.830 --> 18:49.170
and you got the gig.

18:49.170 --> 18:51.710
So...are you
proud of that?

18:51.710 --> 18:54.040
Yes, fool! Yes!

18:56.170 --> 18:58.710
Look.

18:58.710 --> 19:01.250
I was raised by a father
who could only see

19:01.250 --> 19:04.670
the bad things
that could happen.

19:04.670 --> 19:05.710
You know, did that help
with my career?

19:05.710 --> 19:07.080
For sure.

19:07.080 --> 19:08.580
But then I got caught up

19:08.580 --> 19:10.290
in only seeing
the bad things

19:10.290 --> 19:11.580
that could happen
with you,

19:11.580 --> 19:12.620
and I missed out

19:12.620 --> 19:14.540
on the good things
that did happen.

19:15.540 --> 19:18.920
Son, I just
want to say that...

19:18.920 --> 19:20.420
you did great
this week.

19:20.420 --> 19:24.670
♪♪

19:24.670 --> 19:26.170
Can I pour you one?

19:26.170 --> 19:28.420
It's just Sprite and,
uh, Tummy Time Tea,

19:28.420 --> 19:31.080
but, uh,
it'll get you there.

19:31.080 --> 19:32.830
Get me where?
Eh, you know what?

19:32.830 --> 19:34.120
Never mind.

19:34.120 --> 19:35.170
That'll be fine.
I'll take it.

19:35.170 --> 19:36.210
Neat.

19:36.210 --> 19:37.920
Rainbow: Hi!

19:37.920 --> 19:39.580
Guess what, guys!

19:39.580 --> 19:41.920
Kyra has decided

19:41.920 --> 19:43.960
to apply
to Valley Glen Prep.

19:43.960 --> 19:45.420
-What?
-Cool!

19:45.420 --> 19:46.540
Remember who was
there first.

19:46.540 --> 19:49.210
They have a great
science program,

19:49.210 --> 19:51.500
and she's gonna be there
with people that she knows,

19:51.500 --> 19:52.960
'cause of
Jack and Diane.

19:52.960 --> 19:54.830
-Yay!
-Yay!

19:54.830 --> 19:58.380
Such surprising
and expensive news.

19:58.380 --> 20:00.960
And maybe Junior
can donate

20:00.960 --> 20:03.460
some of that
Southland Mutual money.

20:03.460 --> 20:05.790
Ooh.
Yeah!

20:05.790 --> 20:08.210
No!

20:08.210 --> 20:09.460
Yeah!
Okay --

20:09.460 --> 20:11.960
No!

20:11.960 --> 20:13.790
Yeah!!
Dre.

20:14.960 --> 20:16.040
Maybe...

20:16.040 --> 20:16.920
♪♪

20:20.120 --> 20:22.460
Turn off the light, man.

20:22.460 --> 20:24.460
I got to get up
at 5:00 a.m.

20:24.460 --> 20:26.960
Stevens needs a ton of copies
first thing,

20:26.960 --> 20:29.500
and I still got to hook up
Charlie's hippopota-printer.

20:29.500 --> 20:31.580
What a dingus.

20:31.580 --> 20:34.250
Bet you can't wait to not have
to work for those jerks anymore.

20:34.250 --> 20:37.500
Honestly, as crazy
as that place is,

20:37.500 --> 20:40.500
I really enjoy being around
the whole creative process.

20:40.500 --> 20:42.040
You think maybe you
want to major in advertising

20:42.040 --> 20:44.040
when you go to college?

20:44.040 --> 20:47.290
You know...

20:47.290 --> 20:49.670
I don't really know if
I want to go to college anymore.

20:49.670 --> 20:50.670
[ Dramatic music plays ]

20:50.670 --> 20:53.750
[ Groans loudly ]

20:53.750 --> 20:55.040
What's wrong?

20:55.040 --> 20:56.620
[ Straining ]
I don't know what it is.

20:56.620 --> 20:57.580
I just know that it's bad.

20:57.580 --> 20:59.000
Oh, my God!

20:59.000 --> 21:00.080
[ Groans ]
